added.title: Matched
added.description: When a computer dating program matches Beast Boy to Raven, he tries wooing her to disastrous effect.

added.title: Colors of Raven
added.description: A magical prism causes Raven to fragment into five distinct personalities which wreak havoc around town until the other Titans can figure out how to rejoin her.

added.title: The Left Leg
added.description: When the gang bands together to form a giant robot, Robin is relegated to the left leg - but he makes the left leg count!

added.title: Books
added.description: Raven shows the rest of the Titans that books can be fun.

added.title: Lazy Sunday
added.description: When the Titans replace the couch with a treadmill, Cyborg and Beast Boy must get guidance from the couch spirit.

added.title: The Car
added.description: Gumball and Darwin accidentally destroy Mr Robinson's new car...or do they?

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Gumball experiences an impossibly unfortunate chain of events.

added.title: The Microwave
added.description: Gumball and Darwin accidentally create a loveable monster that eats their family.

added.title: The Meddler
added.description: Gumball is embarrassed when Mom comes to school to spend some "quality time".

added.title: The Helmet
added.description: Gumball's magic tinfoil helmet threatens to tear the Watterson family apart!

added.title: Doorway to Helen
added.description: Craig makes a long distance connection with a kid that loves the creek as much as he does.

added.title: The Last Kid in the Creek
added.description: A terrible curse leaves Craig as the only kid in the creek.

added.title: The Climb
added.description: Craig's phone gets stuck in Mt. Sycamore, the tallest tree in the creek!

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Squirrels Squirrels Squirrels
added.description: Courtney's attempt to make Chef a better teacher fails when a squirrel gets his hands on her mind-control device.

added.title: Say Hello to my Little Friends
added.description: After telling the kids he will not miss them over the long weekend Chef locks himself into the school and finds out he was very, very wrong.

added.title: WaterHose-Five
added.description: The hottest day of the year and a broke air conditioner leads to a water battle of epic proportions to determine who controls the garden hose.

added.title: Cody the Barbarian
added.description: Cody is set to inherit a video game empire from his long lost uncle, but only if he and his friends have what it takes to conquer a fantastical live action video game.

added.title: TP2: Judgement Bidet
added.description: When the city experiences a toilet paper shortage Beth and Harold investigate and discover it's their old rival Sewer Mike who is the mastermind behind it all.

added.title: Follow Your Dreams
added.description: Apple and Onion need to find a dream to follow, so that their lives don't head nowhere.

added.title: Sausage and Sweetie Smash
added.description: Onion must stop Apple from falling prey to his obsession, but a certain phone game is proving to be quite an obstacle.

added.title: Selfish Shellfish
added.description: Apple and Onion are faced with a philosophical question: Are they truly doing good deeds for the good of other people or is it all just for them?

added.title: Apple's Formula
added.description: Apple needs to find a formula for comedy that will land him a movie role.

added.title: River of Gold
added.description: Apple and Onion find a mysterious book but they better read it fast before it disappears forever.

added.title: Ocean Gem
added.description: The Ocean disappears on the first day of summer and Beach City is in a panic.

added.title: House Guest
added.description: After injuring his leg, Greg comes to live with Steven and unintentionally interferes with Steven's powers.

added.title: Space Race
added.description: Steven attempts to build a spaceship to let Pearl revisit the wonders of the cosmos.

added.title: Secret Team
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Pearl accidentally pop a bubbled gem and form Secret Team to secretly retrieve the missing shards.

added.title: Island Adventure
added.description: Steven takes Lars and Sadie on a vacation to a magical beach to mend their friendship.

added.title: Out to Launch
added.description: While on a visit to Cape Canaveral, the Tennyson Trio are present for the inaugural launch of an experimental space plane. When Vilgax commandeers the ship, Ben must stop the baddie from weaponizing the shuttle before the countdown hits zero.

added.title: Battle at Biggie Box
added.description: Ben and Billy Billions go head to head over a Sumo Slammer Set sold exclusively inside the world's largest shopping center, only to find six-year-old Simon Sez has gotten it first! A battle royal ensues inside a store that seemingly has everything except an easy to find exit.

added.title: Bon Voyage
added.description: Aboard the SS Pettigrew on its final voyage, Ben must not only battle seasickness but Steam Smythe, who looks to use his mechanical creatures to sink the steamship's modern replacement and the passengers with it!

added.title: Mayhem in Mascot
added.description: After their attempt to get a photo with every storefront mascot is foiled, Ben and Gwen sneak out at night to get their photo with the wooden bear totem known as "Yawk", only to find he and the other mascots have come to life!

added.title: Screamcatcher
added.description: When a cavity forces Ben to the dentist his day gets even worse when the malevolent magician Hex uses a nearby dream catcher to bring our hero's fears to life and transports them both to a nightmarish dreamscape.

added.title: Tourist Trap
added.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: The Alliance
added.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: Breakpoint
added.description: As Wildvine, Ben goes undercover with an alien crime ring and is tempted by their extreme lifestyle.

added.title: The Color of Monkey
added.description: Everybody's favorite alien conman, Argit, takes on a shady sidekick, Simian, in a shocking new business.

added.title: Vreedlemania
added.description: Pa Vreedle reunites with Ma for all-out destruction.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 1
added.description: Alternate dimensions, duplicate Bens and villains from throughout time and space! Just another day in Bellwood.

added.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 2
added.description: Ben and Dr. Psychobos become reluctant allies in a parallel-dimension maelstrom.

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: A thunderstorm forces Chloe to spend the night at the Cave with the Bears. When Chloe's parents tell the Bears to protect Chloe, they take the task a bit too seriously.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Town and Out/Child Fearing
added.description: Town and Out: When the Professor gets a new job, the girls have to move away from Townsville. They try to make the best of it but it's just not the same. In fact, it's downright awful./Child Fearing: When the Mayor needs someone to babysit the girls for him, Mojo is unwittingly drafted. Little does Mojo know, taking care of three little girls can be a big hassle.

added.title: Three Girls and a Monster/Monkey See, Doggy Two
added.description: Three Girls and a Monster: The girls are once again in a furious battle with a ferocious monster. But Blossom and Buttercup can't agree on how to fight the beast and Bubbles just wants everyone to get along./Monkey See, Doggy Two: Mojo has discovered a fatal flaw in his brilliant plan and decides to reenact it step-by-step. The girls think they're experiencing deja vu but it's really just Mojo working his maniacal mischief.

added.title: Gettin' Twiggy with It/Cop Out
added.description: Getting' Twiggy with It: Mitch takes Twiggy, the class hamster, home for the weekend. But when Mitch flushes Twiggy down the toilet, he emerges bigger and badder than ever./Cop Out: A lazy Townsville cop gets fired and blames the girls for saving the day too often, thereby stealing his job. Now, it's payback time and he has the perfect plan to stop those pint-size punks.

added.title: Bubblevision/Bought and Scold
added.description: Bubblevision: Bubbles' fighting has been really terribly lately and the Professor discovers she needs glasses. Bubbles is humiliated by these huge, horrible things and never wants to see or be seen again./Bough and Scold: When Princess buys Townsville, she makes crime legal. Now, the girls have nothing to do and the town is in shambles.

added.title: In the Garden of Good and Eddie
added.description: When the girls try a quick-fix on their neglected veggie garden, they are left with a giant, mooching tomato worm they must care for.

added.title: Road Trippin'
added.description: Realizing her and the Professor don't have much in common, Bubbles schedules a road trip with just the two of them.

added.title: The Big Sleep
added.description: When the Professor's latest invention wreaks havoc in the house, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop it before it escapes.

added.title: The Secret Life of Blossom Powerpuff
added.description: When Blossom can't join her favorite school club, she imagines what her life would be like if she joined other clubs.

added.title: Halt and Catch Silico
added.description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

added.title: It Came From the Nightosphere
added.description: Against Marceline's wishes, Finn conjures her father, the Lord of Evil, and attempts to reconcile their rocky relationship. But when the Lord of Evil discovers his daughter has turned the family axe into a bass guitar, he takes it from her and starts sucking up all the souls in Ooo! Finn must find a way to stop the Lord of Evil and get Marceline's guitar back.

added.title: Loyalty to the King
added.description: There's a new "Nice King" in Ooo, and he looks kinda like someone else we know.

added.title: Blood Under the Skin
added.description: Finn goes on an embarrassing quest to get armor to fit in with some really cool knights.

added.title: The Eyes
added.description: One night, an exhausted Finn and Jake are creeped out by an odd-looking horse that mysteriously appears outside the treehouse and keeps them awake. They try everything they can think of to get rid of the freaky horse, but nothing seems to work.

added.title: Gut Grinder
added.description: Finn and Jake chase a mysterious villain who's been stealing gold from helpless villages.

added.title: Muscle Woman
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby attempt to get Muscle Man and his girlfriend back together, until she begins to fall for Mordecai.

added.title: Temp Check
added.description: Rigby hires a temp to do his work but gets jealous when the temp becomes tight with Mordecai.

added.title: Jinx
added.description: Rigby must figure out how to unjinx himself without talking.

added.title: See You There
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby find out that everyone has been invited by Muscle Man to High Five Ghost's birthday party except them. They decide to go anyway.

added.title: Do Me a Solid
added.description: Mordecai owes Rigby big time when he agrees to go on a double date with him.

added.title: Rough Riders Elementary
added.description: When a corporate sponsorship of Clarence's school turns into an ominous corporate takeover, Clarence must stand up to the the man, no matter how tasty the chicken may be.

added.title: Nothing Ventured
added.description: Clarence and Sumo look to throw together some quick cash so they can invest in Chad and Sumo's dad's new business venture, a boutique sculpture shop.

added.title: Bedside Manners
added.description: After a nasty spill lands Belson in a full body cast, Clarence pays his bedridden friend a visit at the hospital, but what Clarence thinks will cheer him up might actually drive Belson totally crazy!

added.title: Jeff Wins
added.description: Jeff enlists Clarence to help him prepare for the big Aberdale cook-off. Will Jeff keep his cool or freak out and toss his dish away like in years past?

added.title: Suspended
added.description: Clarence and Sumo hit the jackpot when they get suspended for a week, learning all sorts of different facts they'd never learn in class, but after a few days the suspension takes its toll, boredom sets in and the boys want to go back.

added.title: Prank Wars
added.description: When Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus engage in a prank war, Mr. Gus ends up pulling the biggest prank, only realizing too late that it will get Pizza Steve eaten.

added.title: 1992 Called
added.description: Uncle Grandpa travels back to the year 1492 to retrieve a pair of pants.

added.title: Bezt Frends
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to extreme measures to surpass Pizza Steve as Pizza Steve's best friend.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: Greed causes Pizza Steve's latest business venture to backfire.

added.title: Hide and Seek
added.description: A game of hide and seek uncovers a neglected remnant from Uncle Grandpa's past.

added.title: Chair
added.description: Unikitty finds an old, beatup recliner on the curb, but sees its inner beauty and brings it home to introduce to the gang! In a series of absurd and fun vignettes, we discover how a dirty, inanimate chair comes into each of their lives and changes them for the better. We soon learn that dear, sweet Chair was too good for this world.

added.title: Kickflip McPuppycorn
added.description: Puppycorn wants to impress his skater friends with his sweet skills, except he has none. Hoping to boost his confidence, Unikitty and the gang put on Dr. Fox's invisibility suits to secretly help him pull off impossible moves! But they do their job too well and "pro skater" Puppycorn is invited to showcase his skills in a dangerous stunt competition. How far will the gang go to help the pup live out his rad pipe dreams?

added.title: Super Amazing Raft Adventure
added.description: Unikitty and Hawkodile are "lost at sea", stranded on a raft together. Hawkodile sees this as an opportunity to show Unikitty that he's prepared for anything with his expertly-honed survival skills, but to his shock, all of his plans keep falling apart, while Unikitty's silly "it'll all work out, let's have fun" approach is somehow working great! Will Hawkodile manage to let go of his overpreparedness to save them both, or will Unikitty whimsical fun be their doom?

added.title: Tasty Heist
added.description: Richard's prepared one of the tastiest desserts ever, but he's locked it up tight until the friends have their boring dinner. This will not stand. Unikitty organizes a heist, assembling the friends as a crack team to get in, get out, and eat that tasty snack without Richard knowing. But this heist has hiccups. Can the friends take the cake?

added.title: Brawl Bot
added.description: Dr. Fox is proud to unveil her new ultimate combat machine and take it into an underground scientist fighting ring. But Hawkodile's jealous of Dr. Fox's fighting bot that's supposedly a better puncher than him and declares he can beat anything it can. To prove his point, he dresses up in spare robot parts and enters himself secretly in the bot battle. With Unikitty as his fighting coach, can Hawkodile survive the tourney, prove he's tougher than a machine, and avoid the scrap yard?

added.title: The Fatal Fare
added.description: Space Cabbie inadvertently learns about a great threat to the Justice League when one of his passengers turns out to be Darkseid.

added.title: Mxy's Mix-Up
added.description: As the Justice League is trying to protect the United Nations from Grodd's gorilla army, Mr. Mxyptlk pops up from the fifth dimension and thinks it would be great fun to put each of the superheroes' brains into another hero's body.

added.title: Supernatural Adventures in Babysitting
added.description: Stargirl has to enlist Constantine's help when Klarion the Witch Boy takes the place of the boy she's supposed to be babysitting.

added.title: Booster's Gold
added.description: Green Arrow becomes involved with Booster Gold when he discovers that the self-centered superhero has brought dinosaurs back from the past for a money-making venture.

added.title: Boo-ray for Bizarro
added.description: When the diabolical Amazo attacks the League and begins to steal their powers one-by-one, the klutzy, backwards-thinking Bizarro becomes our heroes' last hope to turn things around.

added.title: The Worst Rescue Ever
added.description: The ninja attempt to rescue Cole, but the bickering of his fellow prisoners, the Geckles and Munce, alerts the Skull Sorcerer, and soon the ninja are prisoners too.

added.title: The Two Blades
added.description: In order to escape the Skull Sorcerer's chain-gang, the ninja must convince the Munce and Geckles to put aside their distrust and work together… by promising them something they may not be able to deliver -- The Blades of Deliverance!

added.title: Queen of the Munce
added.description: Jay, Nya and Lloyd are led deep into the Mines of Shintaro by Murt, who brings them back to the Munce "Home- Cave" - a settlement deep in the mountain. There, complications arise when they meet the Munce Queen, Murtessa, who takes a liking to Jay.

added.title: Trial By Mino
added.description: Separated from the others, Kai and Zane discover a party of Geckles who suspect them of being in league with the Skull Sorcerer, and bring them before their leader, Chancellor Gulch, who subjects them to a "Trial-By-Mino."

added.title: The Skull Sorcerer
added.description: Separated from the others, Cole must trust his instincts and make the right choices to find his way to the surface to alert King Vangelis of the dangerous Skull Sorcerer.

added.title: Dangerous Dealings/The Hunter Returns
added.description: Dangerous Dealings: The Awesome Brawler's have become aware of a growing number of adults with illegal Baku-brawling devices. But where are they all coming from? Shun decides to take things into his own hands and sets up a "sting" operation to try to draw out the person selling the devices./The Hunter Returns: Lightning has been caught and locked up by an overly aggressive dog catcher! And to make things worse, he doesn't have his collar with Baku-balls. At the compound where he's being held, he runs into an old foe.  It's up to these two enemies to team up and escape their captor.

added.title: Farewell, Phantom Thief
added.description: After being exposed as a phantom thief in the Bakugan battle league, the Awesome Brawlers are concerned about Ajit, but have no idea of his whereabouts. Dan is particularly affected by Ajit's disappearance and sets out to find him to get some answers./Ajit is out to set right all the wrong doings of his phantom thief past. When he attempts to break into a museum to return artifacts, his mentor Storm is waiting for him. A Bakugan brawl breaks out between two when Storm rolls out his new Bakugan: Cimoga.

added.title: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik/First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik: It's the Haavik Show! Haavik shows up unexpectedly at the practice field and proposes he and Dan play a little game. The Awesome Brawlers have never seen this man before, but they sense something is odd about him. Regardless, when Haavik strokes Dan's ego, there's no way he's backing down from this challenge./First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous: With his back against the wall, Dan tries flipping the script on Haavik by challenging him to a game of his own - a Bakugan Brawl. If Dan wins, then Haavik will have to set him, and the other Awesome Brawler's free.

added.title: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers/The Return of Sophie
added.description: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers: The Awesome brawlers go to see Benton Dusk to tell him about the Fusion Bakugan and ask him if he knows anything about this character: Haavik. However, the meeting takes an unexpected twist when Haavik decides to crash it./The Return of Sophie: A video has surfaced showing Toshi using an illegal Baku-Brawling device! Shun has his hands full when Sophie starts making trouble for Kazami Holdings, accusing them of illegally exploiting Bakugan.

added.title: Wynton's Reality Show/Bakugan Soccer
added.description: Wynton's Reality Show: Lia has had it with Wynton's pranking, but little does she know Wynton is in for a taste of his own medicine. A prank goes too far, and Wynton finds himself in a real-life nightmare with a rampaging Bakugan!/Bakugan Soccer: The Awesome Brawlers and their Bakugan decide to have a game of Bakugan Soccer! The intensity ramps up when Pepe, his teammates and a mysterious coach show up for a little fun. It will take major teamwork for the Awesome Brawlers Bakugan to defeat this rowdy bunch.

added.title: Despeguemos
added.description: De excursión en Cabo Cañaveral, el trío Tennyson presencia el lanzamiento inaugural de una nave espacial experimental, pero cuando Vilgax comanda la nave, Ben debe impedir que el villano use el transbordador como arma antes de que la cuenta regresiva llegue a cero.

added.title: Batalla en El Biggie Box
added.description: Ben y Billy Billions se enfrentan por un set de sumo exclusivo que se vende únicamente en el centro comercial más grande del mundo, isolo para descubrir que Simon Sez, de apenas seis años, lo compró primero! Así se desata una batalla dentro de una tienda que parece tenerlo todo excepto una salida fácil de encontrar.

added.title: Buen Viaje
added.description: Abordo del SS Pettigrew en su último viaje, Ben debe luchar no solo contra el mareo sino también contra Vapor Smythe, que se propone usar a sus criaturas mecánicas para hundir el barco moderno que remplaza al vapor... iy a sus pasajeros!

added.title: Desastre en Mascota
added.description: Frustrado su intento de conseguir una foto con cada mascota de vidriera, Ben y Gwen se escabullen de noche para tomarse su foto con el tótem del oso de madera... iy descubren que él y las demás mascotas cobraron vida!

added.title: Atrapagritos
added.description: Cuando una caries obliga a Ben a ir al dentista, su día empeora aún más cuando el malévolo mago Hex usa un atrapasueños para materializar los miedos de nuestro héroe y los transporta con él a un lugar pesadillesco.

added.title: El Peor Rescate de la Historia
added.description: Los Ninjas intentan rescatar a Cole, pero las discusiones entre prisioneros alertan al Hechicero Calavera, y hace prisioneros a los otros Ninjas.

added.title: Las Dos Espadas
added.description: Para escapar de la prisión del Hechicero Calavera, los Ninjas debe convencer a los Munces y a Geckles de que dejen de discutir y trabajen juntos.

added.title: La Reina de los Munces
added.description: Jay, Nya y Lloyd son guiados entre las minas de Shintaro por Murt, quien los lleva de vuelta a la Cueva de los Munces. A la Reina Munce le gusta Jay.

added.title: Juicio de Mino
added.description: Un grupo de Geckles creen que Kai y Zane están aliados con el Hechicero Calavera y los llevan con su líder, quien los somete a un juicio por Mino…

added.title: El Hechicero Calavera
added.description: Separado de los demás, Cole debe encontrar su camino a la superficie para advertir al Rey Vangelis sobre el peligroso Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: Fallen Arches/The Mane Event
added.description: Fallen Arches: When a gang of old-time villains come out of retirement, the girls enlist the best superhero team of the past to save the city./The Mane Event: Bubbles and Buttercup are playing with Blossom's beautiful locks when an accident happens. Now, Blossom is too embarrassed to put up a good fight.

added.title: Whiteout!
added.description: With the holidays just around the corner, Thomas and Percy are determined to deliver the mail to all the patrons of Sodor. There are presents! The problem is there's a massive whiteout snowstorm covering the entire island and preventing the engines from seeing where they're going. Overcoming various obstacles, Thomas and Percy learn that they can rely on their other senses as well as their familiarity with the island to find where they need to go and deliver the gifts just in time.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Christmas Mountain
added.description: It's Christmas time in Sodor and every engine is excitedly preparing for the holiday, especially Bruno who is excited to put his star on the tree. It's his tradition! When the Christmas tree can't be delivered, Thomas and Percy learn why traditions are important to Bruno. They get creative to keep a disappointed Bruno's holiday spirit bright, ultimately transforming Lookout Mountain into the best -- and biggest -- replacement "tree!" Thomas, Percy, and Bruno are joined by their friends to decorate, sing, and celebrate the tradition together!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Tyrannosaurus Wrecks
added.description: Thomas and the other Engines get to deliver some newly discovered dinosaur bones, but they must deliver them in the correct order for assembly, which isn't as easy as it sounds...
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Super-Long Shortcut
added.description: When Gordon is unable to make an important delivery on his own, Thomas offers his help, but Gordon insists on second-guessing Thomas's every move.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: A Light Delivery
added.description: When Thomas accidentally breaks a light he's hauling to the Sodor Festival of Lights, he learns the best way to be the #1 engine is to be honest when you make a mistake.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Who Said That?
added.description: Daffy learns a bad word and must learn not to use it.

added.title: Let Them Make Cake
added.description: Melissa wants cake, but she wants the other babies to bake it for her.

added.title: Mind Your Manners
added.description: The babies learn proper dinner etiquette when preparing to dine out with Granny.

added.title: Petunia the Piggy Bank
added.description: The kids start getting an allowance but only Petunia thinks to save for something special.

added.title: A Pastime for Petunia
added.description: Petunia has a difficult time finding a hobby that doesn't imitate the other babies' interests.

added.title: Share Your Care
added.description: Dibble plants the seeds of a strange bush outside of its natural environment, unaware that she has unleashed a disaster: The plant multiplies and begins to quickly spread. The Bears must find a way to stop its greedy growth before it crowds out all the other plants in the Silver Lining.

added.title: Return of the Gnomes
added.description: When Gus and Garth's greedy uncle makes his nephews forget the caring, sharing, and generosity they learned from the Care Bears and convinces them to return to their old selfish ways, the Bears must help them remember their caring hearts.

added.title: The Light in the Forest
added.description: Cheer bonds with a migrating firefly-like creature, called a Sparklewing, who stows aboard the Cloudseeker. The two become good friends, but there's a problem: Sparklewings must finish their migration to bring life-giving nutrients to the fields of the Silver Lining. Cheer's difficult and emotional parting with her new friend is only possible once they both accept that it's for a greater good.

added.title: Monsterplant
added.description: Bluster creates a mad scientist's monster from a clump of moss and sends it to scare the Whiffles away. The kindhearted Monsterplant just wants to be friends with them, but the Whiffles are frightened away by how he looks. Share and Dibble work together to show the Whiffles how nice Monsterplant is on the inside.

added.title: Neon Beach Party
added.description: Bluster and his Bad Crowd arrive at a lakeside beach for his summer vacation, unaware that the Care Bears are having their vacation on the opposite shore. Trapped inside Bluster's climate-control dome and forced to spend their vacations together, the Bears must find a way to make friends with their ill-tempered neighbors.

removed.title: Los Maestros Nunca se Rinden
removed.description: Cole, la princesa Vania, Wu y los humildes llegan a un templo, que una vez fue un campo de entrenamiento para los Maestros Elementales de la Tierra.

removed.title: Ataque en el Palacio de los Panqueques
removed.description: Cuando Gwen se inscribe en un concurso de comer panqueques en el mundialmente famoso Palacio de los Panqueques, Ben encuentra a los Bugg Bros. y debe detenerlos antes de que puedan obtener una provisión infinita del elemento que les da vida a sus creaciones: los panqueques del Palacio del Panqueque.

removed.title: Expreso De Gran Estres
removed.description: Durante una transmisión en vivo del nuevo tren bala transcontinental, La Grange se cuela para ganarle al tren. Pero Ben se suma a la diversión, iy no se detendrá ante nada para salir victorioso!

removed.title: Fiesta en el Calabozo
removed.description: Cole, Wu y la Princesa Vania conocen a un grupo de sobrevivientes llamados los de abajo, ellos cuentan cómo terminaron en "Lo más profundo".

removed.title: El Dragon Grief-Bringer
removed.description: Nya y Kai, quienes se han convertido en los líderes de los Munces y Geckles, intentan unirlos para derrotar a su enemigo mutuo, el Hechicero Calavera.

removed.title: Animorfosis
